612
01:19:18.062 --> 01:19:19.855
We can't allow that.

613
01:19:22.025 --> 01:19:25.235
- Is he good?
Who?

614
01:19:25.403 --> 01:19:28.781
- Your opponent.
- Oh, Dr. Tyrell?

615
01:19:28.948 --> 01:19:32.409
I've only beaten him once in chess.
He's a genius.

616
01:19:34.704 --> 01:19:35.704
He designed you.

617
01:19:38.166 --> 01:19:40.709
Maybe he could help.

618
01:19:40.877 --> 01:19:43.420
I'd be happy to mention it to him.

619
01:19:45.548 --> 01:19:49.051
Better if I talk to him in person.

620
01:19:52.138 --> 01:19:57.226
But I understand
he's a sort of hard man to get to.

621
01:19:57.393 --> 01:19:59.311
Yes.

622
01:19:59.479 --> 01:20:01.104
Very.

623
01:20:04.067 --> 01:20:06.443
Will you help us?

624
01:20:07.195 --> 01:20:08.487
I can't.

625
01:20:08.696 --> 01:20:10.656
We need you, Sebastian.

626
01:20:10.824 --> 01:20:13.742
You're our best and only friend.

627
01:20:26.756 --> 01:20:29.216
We're so happy you found us.

628
01:20:31.010 --> 01:20:33.095
I don't think
there's another human being...

629
01:20:33.263 --> 01:20:35.597
...in the whole world
who would've helped us.

630
01:21:24.522 --> 01:21:29.026
66,000 Prosser & Ankovich. Hm.

631
01:21:29.319 --> 01:21:30.736
Trade.

632
01:21:30.904 --> 01:21:33.655
