662
01:23:56.674 --> 01:24:00.010
Would you like to be modified?

663
01:24:00.178 --> 01:24:02.137
Stay here.

664
01:24:07.310 --> 01:24:10.687
Had in mind something
a little more radical.

665
01:24:11.314 --> 01:24:13.315
What...?

666
01:24:13.483 --> 01:24:15.984
What seems to be the problem?

667
01:24:16.319 --> 01:24:18.945
- Death.
- Death.

668
01:24:19.572 --> 01:24:22.657
Well, I'm afraid that's
a little out of my jurisdiction. You...

669
01:24:22.825 --> 01:24:25.827
I want more life...

670
01:24:25.995 --> 01:24:27.245
...father.

671
01:24:32.168 --> 01:24:34.336
The facts of life.

672
01:24:35.713 --> 01:24:38.507
To make an alteration in the...

673
01:24:38.674 --> 01:24:41.093
...evolvement of
an organic life system is fatal.

674
01:24:41.260 --> 01:24:44.846
A coding sequence cannot be revised
once it's been established.

675
01:24:45.014 --> 01:24:46.014
Why not?

676
01:24:46.182 --> 01:24:48.225
Because by the second day
of incubation...

677
01:24:48.392 --> 01:24:52.896
...any cells that have undergone
reversion mutations...

678
01:24:53.064 --> 01:24:57.359
...give rise to revertant colonies
like rats leaving a sinking ship.

679
01:24:57.527 --> 01:24:59.277
Then the ship sinks.

680
01:24:59.487 --> 01:25:03.031
What about EMS recombination?

681
01:25:03.199 --> 01:25:04.699
We've already tried it.

682
01:25:04.867 --> 01:25:09.204
